## 4. â— Handling Errors

### ğŸ§Š Cold Start Behavior

When `DesiredCopyCount = 0`, SageMaker terminates the IC's backing instance. Upon next request:

| Event              | Result                                           |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Request received   | Triggers cold start (infra + container + model) |
| Latency            | ~20â€“90 seconds                                   |
| Response           | Eventually returns successfully                  |
| Reuse              | Subsequent calls are fast (IC is warm)           |

### ğŸ” Monitor Metrics

| Metric                         | Purpose                                 |
|-------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| `DesiredCopyCount = 0`        | IC has scaled to zero                   |
| `NoCapacityInvocationFailures`| Request arrived during cold start       |
| CloudWatch Logs               | Show startup and model load time        |

> ğŸ’¡ Tip: Set `MinCapacity=1` to keep the IC warm during peak hours.

---

## 5. âš ï¸ Limitations

| Constraint                                 | Description                                                      |
|--------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|
| âŒ Cannot upgrade non-IC endpoint           | Must delete and recreate endpoint to use Inference Components   |
| âŒ Cannot remove IC once attached           | Endpoint stays IC-based once created                            |
| ğŸš« No multi-model routing in this setup     | Single IC only (no variant traffic splitting)                   |
| â± Cold start latency                       | 20â€“90 seconds when scaled to zero                               |
| ğŸ›  IC name should match endpoint name       | Simplifies management and invocation                            |

